      • findAllVotingInfo

        public Cancelable findAllVotingInfo(java.lang.String searchTerm,
                                    SearchMinerVotingOrder order,
                                    MinerObjectId id,
                                    java.lang.String accountName,
                                    boolean onlyMyVotes,
                                    int limit,
                                    Callback<java.util.List> callback)

        Get miner voting info list by account that match search term.

        Parameters:
        searchTerm - miner name
        order - available options are defined in enum SearchMinerVotingOrder
        id - the object id of the miner to start searching from, 1.4.* or null when start from beginning
        accountName - account name or null when searching without account
        onlyMyVotes - when true it selects only votes given by account
        limit - maximum number of miners info to fetch (must not exceed 1000)
        callback - a callback object that asynchronously receives the result value or error
        Returns:
        a request handler object which can be used to cancel the request

      • createVoteOperation

        public Cancelable createVoteOperation(AccountObjectId accountId,
                                      java.util.List<ch.decent.sdk.model.MinerObjectId> minerIds,
                                      Fee fee,
                                      Callback<ch.decent.sdk.model.operation.AccountUpdateOperation> callback)

        Create vote for miner operation. For more options see class AccountUpdateOperation constructor.

        Parameters:
        accountId - account object id, 1.2.*
        minerIds - list of miner account ids
        fee - {@link AssetAmount} fee for the operation or asset id, if left undefined the fee will be computed in DCT asset. When set, the request might fail if the asset is not convertible to DCT or conversion pool is not large enough

        a request handler object which can be used to cancel the request

      • createMinerCreateOperation

        public Cancelable createMinerCreateOperation(AccountObjectId accountId,
                                             java.lang.String url,
                                             Fee fee,
                                             Callback<ch.decent.sdk.model.operation.MinerCreateOperation> callback)

        Create miner create operation. Account primary public key is used as miner's public key. For more options see class MinerCreateOperation constructor.

        Parameters:
        accountId - account object id, 1.2.*. The account which owns the miner. This account pays the fee for this operation.
        url - url pointing to miner info web page
        fee - {@link AssetAmount} fee for the operation or asset id, if left undefined the fee will be computed in DCT asset. When set, the request might fail if the asset is not convertible to DCT or conversion pool is not large enough
        callback - a callback object that asynchronously receives the result value or error
        Returns:
        a request handler object which can be used to cancel the request
        See Also:
        class MinerCreateOperation

                         Address signingKey,
                         Fee fee,
                         Callback<ch.decent.sdk.model.TransactionConfirmation> callback)

        Update accounts's miner.

        Parameters:

        callback - a callback object that asynchronously receives the result value or error
        Returns:
        a request handler object which can be used to cancel the request
